      "value": "What is State Management?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "State management refers to handling and sharing data across components in a Vue application."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Types of State"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Type", "Description"],
        "rows": [
          ["Local State", "State inside a component"],
          ["Shared State", "State shared via props or events"],
          ["Global State", "State shared across entire app"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Using Props and Events"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Props pass data down, and events ($emit) send data up between components."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Provide & Inject"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "javascript",
      "value": "provide() {\n  return { message: 'Hello' };\n},\ninject: ['message']"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Pinia (Recommended)"
